# Filled Density Plot
d <- density(schnum$age)
plot(d, main="Distribution of age")
polygon(d, col="red", border="blue")

#age is left skewed : impying that mean is less than mode
d <- density(schnum$absences)
plot(d, main="Distribution of absences")
polygon(d, col="red", border="blue")

#Absence is left skewed
d <- density(schnum$G1)
plot(d, main="Distribution of G1")
polygon(d, col="red", border="blue")

#G1 is right skewed : impying that mean is more than mode

3 b. Regression models using some predictors from provided in three sets

#model1
set1<-c("school","sex","age","address","Pstatus","Medu","Fedu","Mjob", "Fjob","traveltime", "studytime", "failures", "absences","G1", "G2","G3")
newset1 <- school[set1]

# load the library
library(caret)
## Loading required package: lattice
# define training control
train_control <- trainControl(method="LOOCV")
# train the model
model <- train(G3~., data=newset1, trControl=train_control, method="lm")
# summarize results
print(model)
